results.name: Expansion of Product_{k>=1} (1-x^(k^3)).
comment: The difference between the number of partitions of n into an even number of distinct cubes and the number of partitions of n into an odd number of distinct cubes. - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Jan 15 2018
link: Vaclav Kotesovec, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..100000
mathematica: nmax = 1000; nn = Floor[nmax^(1/3)]+1; poly = ConstantArray[0, nn^3 + 1]; poly[[1]] = 1; poly[[2]] = -1; poly[[3]] = 0; Do[Do[poly[[j + 1]] -= poly[[j - k^3 + 1]], {j, nn^3, k^3, -1}];, {k, 2, nn}]; Take[poly, nmax+1]
results.author: _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Dec 13 2016
